This paper discusses the use of Information-Centric Fog Computing and network topology, which suggests a focus on networking and distributed systems (cs.NI, cs.DC). The paper also introduces a new metric for measuring node centrality based on content, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed metric through simulations, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
